  "detector.precisionDesc": "How closely the image must match (50–100%). Lower values detect more but risk false positives. Recommended: 55–70%.",
  "detector.cooldownDesc": "Minimum pause after a match. Prevents double-counting. After the cooldown, the system also waits for the match to disappear (hysteresis).",
  "detector.hysteresis": "Hysteresis threshold",
  "detector.hysteresisDesc": "Percentage of precision the score must drop below after a match before a new match can be detected",
  "detector.cooldownHint": "Hysteresis: After cooldown, the score must drop below {{pct}}% of precision before a new match can count.",
  "detector.hitsDesc": "How many consecutive frames must match before an encounter is counted. 1 is usually enough; higher values reduce false positives.",
